 {"@type": "Question", "name": "What is Qi2 vs Qi?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Qi2 is the second generation of the Qi wireless charging standard, adding magnetic alignment (MPP - Magnetic Power Profile) and 15W universal fast charging. It's based on Apple's MagSafe technology and works with iPhone 12-16 series natively."}},
 {"@type": "Question", "name": "What is the MOQ for Qi2 wireless power banks?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "MOQ starts at 500 units for standard ODM models with custom logo. Custom OEM with new tooling: 1,000-2,000 units. Sample turnaround 7-10 days."}},
 {"@type": "Question", "name": "Are these MagSafe compatible?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. Qi2 is built on Apple's MagSafe standard. Our power banks use N52H neodymium magnets for the same alignment strength as Apple's MagSafe accessories."}},
 {"@type": "Question", "name": "Can it charge through a phone case?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes, through cases up to 4mm thick. For magnetic alignment, the case must be MagSafe-compatible (most premium cases support this). Pure plastic cases without metal interference work universally."}},
 {"@type": "Question", "name": "What is the difference between Qi2 and MagSafe?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Qi2 is the open standard version of MagSafe, managed by WPC (Wireless Power Consortium). MagSafe is Apple's proprietary implementation. Both use the same magnetic ring and 15W speed. Qi2 works cross-platform: iPhone 12-16 + Android phones like Samsung Galaxy S25 and Google Pixel 10. For OEM buyers, Qi2 certification means your product works with all MagSafe accessories."}},
 {"@type": "Question", "name": "Which Android phones support Qi2 magnetic charging?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "As of mid-2026, Samsung Galaxy S25 series and Google Pixel 10 series are the first major Android flagships with native Qi2 magnetic support. More manufacturers are expected in 2026 H2. This means Qi2 magnetic power banks now address both iPhone AND Android premium users — doubling the addressable market."}},
 {"@type": "Question", "name": "What is N52H magnet and why does it matter?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "N52H is a grade of neodymium magnet with maximum energy product (BH max) of 52 MGOe and a working temperature up to 120°C. Standard N52 only handles 60°C. Since wireless charging generates heat, N52H prevents demagnetization during prolonged charging sessions — maintaining alignment strength over the product's lifetime."}},
 {"@type": "Question", "name": "What is Qi2.2 and 25W wireless charging?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Qi2.2 is the latest WPC standard (released 2025) enabling 25W magnetic wireless charging — a 67% speed increase over Qi2's 15W. First Qi2.2 products launched in 2026 from Belkin, EcoFlow, and Baseus. WOWOHCOOL offers Qi2.2 25W OEM models for brands wanting next-gen speed positioning."}}
