<!-- What is Qi2 -->
<section class="sec bg-white relative py-16">
 <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6">
 <h2 class="section-title text-center">What Is Qi2 Wireless Magnetic Charging?</h2>
 <p class="text-center text-slate-500 text-sm max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-8">Qi2 is the next generation of the Qi wireless charging standard, built on Apple's MagSafe technology. It adds magnetic alignment via N52H neodymium magnets and 15W universal fast charging across all phone brands.</p>

 <blockquote class="max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-12 bg-brandOrange/5 border-l-4 border-brandOrange rounded-r-xl px-6 py-5 text-sm text-slate-700 italic leading-relaxed">
  <p>"The magnetic wireless power bank market is projected to grow from $1.85 billion in 2024 to $3.79 billion by 2031 at a 10.8% CAGR. By December 2025, over 2,665 Qi2-certified products were on the market, with power banks representing 23% of all certifications — 609 models. The WPC projects nearly 4 billion Qi2 devices will ship within five years. With Qi2.2 enabling 25W wireless charging and Samsung Galaxy S25 plus Google Pixel 10 adding native Android magnetic support, the addressable market for cross-platform magnetic power banks has effectively doubled overnight."</p>
