<!-- N52H Magnet Technology -->
<section class="sec bg-slate-50 relative py-16">
 <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6">
 <h2 class="text-3xl lg:text-4xl font-black text-brandBlue uppercase italic tracking-tighter mb-4 text-center">N52H Magnet Technology: <span class="text-brandOrange">Why Grade Matters</span></h2>
 <p class="text-center text-slate-500 text-sm max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-12">All WOWOHCOOL Qi2 power banks use N52H neodymium magnets — not the cheaper N35 or N48 found in budget products. Here's why the H grade matters for wireless charging reliability.</p>

 <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
 <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-200 shadow-sm">
 <h3 class="font-black text-brandBlue uppercase mb-3 text-sm">N52 (Standard)</h3>
 <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-slate-600">
 <li>&bull; BH(max): 52 MGOe</li>
 <li>&bull; Max working temp: <strong class="text-red-500">60°C</strong></li>
 <li>&bull; Risk: Wireless charging heats to 40-55°C — near thermal limit</li>
 <li>&bull; Over time: Gradual demagnetization = weaker snap</li>
 </ul>
 </div>
 <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-brandOrange/30 shadow-sm ring-1 ring-brandOrange/20">
 <h3 class="font-black text-brandOrange uppercase mb-3 text-sm">N52H (WOWOHCOOL Standard)</h3>
 <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-slate-600">
 <li>&bull; BH(max): 52 MGOe (same strength)</li>
 <li>&bull; Max working temp: <strong class="text-green-600">120°C</strong></li>
 <li>&bull; 2x thermal headroom above charging temps</li>
 <li>&bull; Zero demagnetization risk over product lifetime</li>
 </ul>
 </div>
 </div>
 <p class="text-center text-xs text-slate-400 mt-6">N52H costs 15-20% more than N52 but eliminates the #1 cause of magnetic power bank warranty returns: weakened alignment after 6-12 months of use.</p>
 </div>
</section>

