<!-- FAQ -->
<section class="sec bg-slate-50 relative py-16">
 <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6">
 <h2 class="text-3xl lg:text-4xl font-black text-slate-900 uppercase italic tracking-tighter mb-10 text-center">Wireless / Magnetic <span class="text-brandOrange">FAQ</span></h2>
 <div class="space-y-4">
 <details class="bg-white rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 group">
 <summary class="font-black text-slate-900 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center text-sm uppercase">What is Qi2 vs Qi?<span class="text-brandOrange group-open:rotate-180 transition">&#9660;</span></summary>
 <p class="faq-answer text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">Qi2 is the second generation of the Qi wireless charging standard, adding magnetic alignment (MPP - Magnetic Power Profile) and 15W universal fast charging. It's based on Apple's MagSafe technology and works with iPhone 12-16 series natively.</p>
 </details>
 <details class="bg-white rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 group">
 <summary class="font-black text-slate-900 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center text-sm uppercase">What is the MOQ for Qi2 wireless power banks?<span class="text-brandOrange group-open:rotate-180 transition">&#9660;</span></summary>
 <p class="faq-answer text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">MOQ starts at 500 units for standard ODM models with custom logo. Custom OEM with new tooling: 1,000-2,000 units. Sample turnaround 7-10 days for pre-production samples.</p>
 </details>
 <details class="bg-white rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 group">
 <summary class="font-black text-slate-900 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center text-sm uppercase">Are these MagSafe compatible?<span class="text-brandOrange group-open:rotate-180 transition">&#9660;</span></summary>
 <p class="faq-answer text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">Yes. Qi2 is built on Apple's MagSafe standard. Our power banks use N52H neodymium magnets for the same alignment strength as Apple's MagSafe accessories.</p>
 </details>
 <details class="bg-white rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 group">
 <summary class="font-black text-slate-900 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center text-sm uppercase">Can it charge through a phone case?<span class="text-brandOrange group-open:rotate-180 transition">&#9660;</span></summary>
 <p class="faq-answer text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">Yes, through cases up to 4mm thick. For magnetic alignment, the case must be MagSafe-compatible (most premium cases support this). Pure plastic cases without metal interference work universally.</p>
 </details>
 <details class="bg-white rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 group">
 <summary class="font-black text-slate-900 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center text-sm uppercase">What is the difference between Qi2 and MagSafe?<span class="text-brandOrange group-open:rotate-180 transition">&#9660;</span></summary>
 <p class="faq-answer text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">Qi2 is the open standard version of MagSafe, managed by WPC (Wireless Power Consortium). MagSafe is Apple's proprietary implementation. Both use the same magnetic ring and 15W speed, but Qi2 works cross-platform — iPhone 12-16 plus Android phones like Samsung Galaxy S25 and Google Pixel 10. For OEM buyers, Qi2 certification means your product is automatically MagSafe-compatible without needing Apple MFi licensing.</p>
 </details>
 <details class="bg-white rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 group">
 <summary class="font-black text-slate-900 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center text-sm uppercase">Which Android phones support Qi2 magnetic charging?<span class="text-brandOrange group-open:rotate-180 transition">&#9660;</span></summary>
 <p class="faq-answer text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">As of mid-2026, Samsung Galaxy S25 series and Google Pixel 10 series support native Qi2 magnetic alignment. More Android flagships are expected in 2026 H2. This means Qi2 magnetic power banks now address both iPhone AND Android premium users — effectively doubling the total addressable market for your brand.</p>
 </details>
 <details class="bg-white rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 group">
 <summary class="font-black text-slate-900 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center text-sm uppercase">What is N52H magnet and why does it matter?<span class="text-brandOrange group-open:rotate-180 transition">&#9660;</span></summary>
 <p class="faq-answer text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">N52H is a neodymium magnet grade with 52 MGOe energy and a working temperature up to 120°C (vs 60°C for standard N52). Since wireless charging generates 40-55°C heat, N52H prevents demagnetization during prolonged charging — maintaining snap alignment strength over the product's full lifetime. Budget competitors using N52 or N48 magnets often develop weak alignment within 6-12 months.</p>
 </details>
 <details class="bg-white rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 group">
 <summary class="font-black text-slate-900 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center text-sm uppercase">What is Qi2.2 and 25W wireless charging?<span class="text-brandOrange group-open:rotate-180 transition">&#9660;</span></summary>
 <p class="faq-answer text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">Qi2.2 is the latest WPC standard (released 2025) enabling 25W magnetic wireless charging — a 67% speed increase over Qi2's 15W. First Qi2.2 products launched in 2026 from Belkin, EcoFlow, and Baseus. It's backward-compatible with existing Qi2 15W devices. WOWOHCOOL offers Qi2.2 25W OEM models for brands wanting next-gen speed positioning.</p>
 </details>
 </div>
 </div>
</section>

